Hi,

According to the documentation: 
https://github.com/reactor/reactor-core/blob/main/docs/asciidoc/metrics-details.adoc

Supplying an observation factory we can configure any attributes of the observation.

However, using contextualName is always overridden by sequence name.  E.g.:
```java
Mono<String> userName(String userId) {
		return Mono.defer(() -> {
			log.info("Getting user name for user with id <{}>", userId);
			return Mono.delay(Duration.ofMillis(random.nextLong(200L)))
					.thenReturn("foo");
			})
				.tap(Micrometer.observation(registry, r -> Observation.createNotStarted("user.name", registry)
						.lowCardinalityKeyValue("userType", "admin")
						.highCardinalityKeyValue("userId", userId)
						.contextualName("getting-user-name")));
	}
```

Results in "reactor.observation" observation/span.

Note: observation can be also created convention, which can also populate name / contextual name.

https://github.com/reactor/reactor-core/blob/5553aa80137482ec26acb960f4d4f42b8a44da94/reactor-core-micrometer/src/main/java/reactor/core/observability/micrometer/MicrometerObservationListener.java#L101

Can we move contextualName setter into defaultObservation in case if there is no custom created observation?

Thanks,
Artyom
